Paper: hep-th/9402042

Date: 1994-02-08

Title: Toward the Universal Theory of Strings

Authors: Fiorenzo Bastianelli, Nobuyoshi Ohta and Jens Lyng Petersen

Comments: Latex file, 8 pages, NBI-HET-94-08. The preprint number is changed

and one reference is addedJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B327 (1994) 35-39

We show that the $N=2$ superstrings may be viewed as a special class of the$N=4$ superstrings and demonstrate their equivalence. This allows us to realizeall known string theories based on linear algebras and with $N<4$supersymmetries as special choices of the vacua in the $N=4$ superstring.